UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 900
1 AN ACT relating to the practice of audiology.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 334A.020 is amended to read as follows:
4 As used in this chapter, unless the context otherwise requires:
5 (1) "Assisting in the practice of speech pathology" means the provision of certain
6 specific components of a speech or language service program provided by a speech-
7 language pathology assistant under the supervision and direction of an appropriately
8 qualified supervisor;
9 (2) "Audiologist" means one who is licensed to practice audiology. An audiologist may
10 describe himself or herself to the public by any title or description of services
11 incorporating the words "audiologist," "audiology," "audiological," "hearing
12 center," "hearing clinic," "hearing clinician," "hearing therapist," "audiometry,"
13 "audiometrist," "audiometrics," "otometry," "otometrist," "aural rehabilitationist,"
14 or "hearing conservationist";
15 (3) "Board" means the Kentucky Board of Speech-Language Pathology and Audiology;
16 (4) "Continuing professional education" in speech-language pathology and audiology
17 consists of planned learning experiences beyond a basic educational program
18 leading to a degree. These experiences are designed to promote knowledge, skills,
19 and attitudes of speech-language pathology and audiology practitioners to enable
20 them to provide professional services in their areas of training that are based on
21 current research and best practices;
22 (5) "Interim license" means a license issued by the board pursuant to KRS 334A.035 to
23 a person for the purpose of completing the supervised postgraduate professional
24 experience required under that section prior to an application for licensure as a
25 speech-language pathologist or a speech-language pathology assistant;
26 (6) "Person" means any individual, organization, or corporate body, except that only
27 individuals can be licensed under this chapter;
