1 offending party to penalties established in KRS 334A.990;
2 (12)[(11)] "Supervisor" means a person who holds a Kentucky license as a speech-
3 language pathologist or who holds Education Professional Standards Board master's
4 level certification as a teacher of exceptional children in the areas of speech and
5 communication disorders as established by administrative regulation; and
6 (13)[(12)] "Temporary license" means a license that may be issued by the board
7 administrator pursuant to KRS 334A.181 to any applicant who has met all the
8 requirements for permanent licensure in accordance with that section.
